{
  // Running a service from a plain Node script — how every phase has been
  // verified against the real database — needs two modules shimmed:
  //
  //   • `server-only` throws outside a React Server Component graph.
  //   • `next/font/google` is a build-time transform with no runtime impl.
  //
  // Both are reached through the template registry, which `event-service`
  // imports. tsx resolves them via CJS, so an ESM `register()` loader hook is
  // never consulted — tsconfig `paths` is what actually works.
  //
  //   pnpm exec tsx --tsconfig tsconfig.script.json <script>.ts
  //
  // Do NOT reach for `--conditions=react-server`: it also swaps React for a
  // build with no `createContext`, and lucide-react dies on import.
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"],
      "server-only": ["./node_modules/server-only/empty.js"],
      "next/font/google": ["./scripts/stubs/next-font-google.ts"]
    }
  }
}
